{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":787,"text":"I'm going to begin with a scary question:"},{"time":3659,"text":"Are we headed toward\na future without jobs?"},{"time":6987,"text":"The remarkable progress that we're seeing"},{"time":9080,"text":"in technologies like self-driving cars"},{"time":10965,"text":"has led to an explosion\nof interest in this question,"},{"time":14054,"text":"but because it's something\nthat's been asked"},{"time":16228,"text":"so many times in the past,"},{"time":17508,"text":"maybe what we should really be asking"},{"time":19372,"text":"is whether this time is really different."},{"time":23252,"text":"The fear that automation\nmight displace workers"},{"time":26237,"text":"and potentially lead\nto lots of unemployment"},{"time":28378,"text":"goes back at a minimum 200 years\nto the Luddite revolts in England."},{"time":32290,"text":"And since then, this concern\nhas come up again and again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35510,"text":"I'm going to guess"},{"time":36695,"text":"that most of you have probably never\nheard of the Triple Revolution report,"},{"time":41185,"text":"but this was a very prominent report."},{"time":43502,"text":"It was put together\nby a brilliant group of people --"},{"time":46057,"text":"it actually included\ntwo Nobel laureates --"},{"time":49138,"text":"and this report was presented\nto the President of the United States,"},{"time":52385,"text":"and it argued that the US was on the brink\nof economic and social upheaval"},{"time":57903,"text":"because industrial automation\nwas going to put millions of people"},{"time":61029,"text":"out of work."},{"time":62205,"text":"Now, that report was delivered\nto President Lyndon Johnson"},{"time":65886,"text":"in March of 1964."},{"time":67711,"text":"So that's now over 50 years,"},{"time":69951,"text":"and, of course, that\nhasn't really happened."},{"time":72033,"text":"And that's been the story again and again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74201,"text":"This alarm has been raised repeatedly,"},{"time":76334,"text":"but it's always been a false alarm."},{"time":78371,"text":"And because it's been a false alarm,"},{"time":80204,"text":"it's led to a very conventional way\nof thinking about this."},{"time":83035,"text":"And that says essentially that yes,"},{"time":85591,"text":"technology may devastate\nentire industries."},{"time":88163,"text":"It may wipe out whole occupations\nand types of work."},{"time":91919,"text":"But at the same time, of course,"},{"time":93551,"text":"progress is going to lead\nto entirely new things."},{"time":95926,"text":"So there will be new industries\nthat will arise in the future,"},{"time":98912,"text":"and those industries, of course,\nwill have to hire people."},{"time":101794,"text":"There'll be new kinds of work\nthat will appear,"},{"time":104056,"text":"and those might be things that today\nwe can't really even imagine."},{"time":107290,"text":"And that has been the story so far,"},{"time":109061,"text":"and it's been a positive story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111095,"text":"It turns out that the new jobs\nthat have been created"},{"time":114444,"text":"have generally been\na lot better than the old ones."},{"time":116938,"text":"They have, for example,\nbeen more engaging."},{"time":119618,"text":"They've been in safer,\nmore comfortable work environments,"},{"time":123071,"text":"and, of course, they've paid more."},{"time":124775,"text":"So it has been a positive story."},{"time":126664,"text":"That's the way things\nhave played out so far."},{"time":129292,"text":"But there is one particular\nclass of worker"},{"time":132264,"text":"for whom the story\nhas been quite different."},{"time":135938,"text":"For these workers,"},{"time":137112,"text":"technology has completely\ndecimated their work,"},{"time":140157,"text":"and it really hasn't created\nany new opportunities at all."},{"time":143395,"text":"And these workers, of course,"},{"time":145614,"text":"are horses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146926,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":148393,"text":"So I can ask a very provocative question:"},{"time":151167,"text":"Is it possible that at some\npoint in the future,"},{"time":154626,"text":"a significant fraction of the human\nworkforce is going to be made redundant"},{"time":159278,"text":"in the way that horses were?"},{"time":161485,"text":"Now, you might have a very visceral,\nreflexive reaction to that."},{"time":164509,"text":"You might say, \"That's absurd."},{"time":166180,"text":"How can you possibly compare\nhuman beings to horses?\""},{"time":170437,"text":"Horses, of course, are very limited,"},{"time":172230,"text":"and when cars and trucks\nand tractors came along,"},{"time":175147,"text":"horses really had nowhere else to turn."},{"time":177844,"text":"People, on the other hand,\nare intelligent;"},{"time":180228,"text":"we can learn, we can adapt."},{"time":182037,"text":"And in theory,"},{"time":183225,"text":"that ought to mean that we can\nalways find something new to do,"},{"time":186376,"text":"and that we can always remain\nrelevant to the future economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189706,"text":"But here's the really\ncritical thing to understand."},{"time":192790,"text":"The machines that will threaten\nworkers in the future"},{"time":195679,"text":"are really nothing like those cars\nand trucks and tractors"},{"time":198937,"text":"that displaced horses."},{"time":200577,"text":"The future is going to be full\nof thinking, learning, adapting machines."},{"time":205440,"text":"And what that really means"},{"time":206872,"text":"is that technology is finally\nbeginning to encroach"},{"time":209730,"text":"on that fundamental human capability --"},{"time":212603,"text":"the thing that makes us\nso different from horses,"},{"time":215430,"text":"and the very thing that, so far,"},{"time":217688,"text":"has allowed us to stay ahead\nof the march of progress"},{"time":220359,"text":"and remain relevant,"},{"time":221572,"text":"and, in fact, indispensable\nto the economy."},{"time":226407,"text":"So what is it that is really so different"},{"time":228926,"text":"about today's information technology"},{"time":230993,"text":"relative to what we've seen in the past?"},{"time":232964,"text":"I would point to three fundamental things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235641,"text":"The first thing is that we have seen\nthis ongoing process"},{"time":240074,"text":"of exponential acceleration."},{"time":242420,"text":"I know you all know about Moore's law,"},{"time":244539,"text":"but in fact, it's more\nbroad-based than that;"},{"time":246859,"text":"it extends in many cases,\nfor example, to software,"},{"time":250033,"text":"it extends to communications,\nbandwidth and so forth."},{"time":253057,"text":"But the really key thing to understand"},{"time":255065,"text":"is that this acceleration has now\nbeen going on for a really long time."},{"time":258960,"text":"In fact, it's been going on for decades."},{"time":260909,"text":"If you measure from the late 1950s,"},{"time":263689,"text":"when the first integrated\ncircuits were fabricated,"},{"time":266138,"text":"we've seen something on the order\nof 30 doublings in computational power"},{"time":270947,"text":"since then."},{"time":272127,"text":"That's just an extraordinary number\nof times to double any quantity,"},{"time":275839,"text":"and what it really means"},{"time":277103,"text":"is that we're now at a point\nwhere we're going to see"},{"time":279651,"text":"just an extraordinary amount\nof absolute progress,"},{"time":282086,"text":"and, of course, things are going\nto continue to also accelerate"},{"time":285085,"text":"from this point."},{"time":286268,"text":"So as we look forward\nto the coming years and decades,"},{"time":288832,"text":"I think that means\nthat we're going to see things"},{"time":291194,"text":"that we're really not prepared for."},{"time":292891,"text":"We're going to see things\nthat astonish us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294992,"text":"The second key thing"},{"time":296282,"text":"is that the machines are,\nin a limited sense, beginning to think."},{"time":300212,"text":"And by this, I don't mean human-level AI,"},{"time":302693,"text":"or science fiction\nartificial intelligence;"},{"time":305653,"text":"I simply mean that machines and algorithms\nare making decisions."},{"time":310139,"text":"They're solving problems,\nand most importantly, they're learning."},{"time":314023,"text":"In fact, if there's one technology\nthat is truly central to this"},{"time":317350,"text":"and has really become\nthe driving force behind this,"},{"time":320451,"text":"it's machine learning,"},{"time":321647,"text":"which is just becoming\nthis incredibly powerful,"},{"time":324391,"text":"disruptive, scalable technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327561,"text":"One of the best examples\nI've seen of that recently"},{"time":330054,"text":"was what Google's DeepMind\ndivision was able to do"},{"time":332829,"text":"with its AlphaGo system."},{"time":334406,"text":"Now, this is the system that was able\nto beat the best player in the world"},{"time":338730,"text":"at the ancient game of Go."},{"time":340733,"text":"Now, at least to me,"},{"time":341907,"text":"there are two things that really\nstand out about the game of Go."},{"time":345048,"text":"One is that as you're playing the game,"},{"time":347368,"text":"the number of configurations\nthat the board can be in"},{"time":350258,"text":"is essentially infinite."},{"time":351693,"text":"There are actually more possibilities\nthan there are atoms in the universe."},{"time":355980,"text":"So what that means is,"},{"time":357188,"text":"you're never going to be able to build\na computer to win at the game of Go"},{"time":360809,"text":"the way chess was approached, for example,"},{"time":363013,"text":"which is basically to throw\nbrute-force computational power at it."},{"time":367563,"text":"So clearly, a much more sophisticated,\nthinking-like approach is needed."},{"time":372368,"text":"The second thing\nthat really stands out is that,"},{"time":375663,"text":"if you talk to one\nof the championship Go players,"},{"time":378334,"text":"this person cannot necessarily\neven really articulate what exactly it is"},{"time":382843,"text":"they're thinking about\nas they play the game."},{"time":385082,"text":"It's often something\nthat's very intuitive,"},{"time":387299,"text":"it's almost just like a feeling\nabout which move they should make."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390645,"text":"So given those two qualities,"},{"time":392076,"text":"I would say that playing Go\nat a world champion level"},{"time":396037,"text":"really ought to be something\nthat's safe from automation,"},{"time":399299,"text":"and the fact that it isn't should really\nraise a cautionary flag for us."},{"time":403769,"text":"And the reason is that we tend\nto draw a very distinct line,"},{"time":407710,"text":"and on one side of that line\nare all the jobs and tasks"},{"time":411243,"text":"that we perceive as being on some level\nfundamentally routine and repetitive"},{"time":416015,"text":"and predictable."},{"time":417389,"text":"And we know that these jobs\nmight be in different industries,"},{"time":420271,"text":"they might be in different occupations\nand at different skill levels,"},{"time":423668,"text":"but because they are innately predictable,"},{"time":425902,"text":"we know they're probably at some point\ngoing to be susceptible"},{"time":429053,"text":"to machine learning,"},{"time":430254,"text":"and therefore, to automation."},{"time":431697,"text":"And make no mistake --\nthat's a lot of jobs."},{"time":433818,"text":"That's probably something\non the order of roughly half"},{"time":436521,"text":"the jobs in the economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438112,"text":"But then on the other side of that line,"},{"time":440295,"text":"we have all the jobs\nthat require some capability"},{"time":444390,"text":"that we perceive as being uniquely human,"},{"time":446786,"text":"and these are the jobs\nthat we think are safe."},{"time":449033,"text":"Now, based on what I know\nabout the game of Go,"},{"time":451322,"text":"I would've guessed that it really ought\nto be on the safe side of that line."},{"time":455049,"text":"But the fact that it isn't,\nand that Google solved this problem,"},{"time":458251,"text":"suggests that that line is going\nto be very dynamic."},{"time":460707,"text":"It's going to shift,"},{"time":461910,"text":"and it's going to shift in a way\nthat consumes more and more jobs and tasks"},{"time":466069,"text":"that we currently perceive\nas being safe from automation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469921,"text":"The other key thing to understand"},{"time":471602,"text":"is that this is by no means just about\nlow-wage jobs or blue-collar jobs,"},{"time":476764,"text":"or jobs and tasks done by people"},{"time":478663,"text":"that have relatively\nlow levels of education."},{"time":480791,"text":"There's lots of evidence to show"},{"time":482339,"text":"that these technologies are rapidly\nclimbing the skills ladder."},{"time":485523,"text":"So we already see an impact\non professional jobs --"},{"time":489163,"text":"tasks done by people like accountants,"},{"time":493622,"text":"financial analysts,"},{"time":494963,"text":"journalists,"},{"time":496283,"text":"lawyers, radiologists and so forth."},{"time":498684,"text":"So a lot of the assumptions that we make"},{"time":500646,"text":"about the kind of occupations\nand tasks and jobs"},{"time":503890,"text":"that are going to be threatened\nby automation in the future"},{"time":506733,"text":"are very likely to be\nchallenged going forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508955,"text":"So as we put these trends together,"},{"time":510679,"text":"I think what it shows is that we could\nvery well end up in a future"},{"time":513995,"text":"with significant unemployment."},{"time":516254,"text":"Or at a minimum,"},{"time":517430,"text":"we could face lots of underemployment\nor stagnant wages,"},{"time":521235,"text":"maybe even declining wages."},{"time":524142,"text":"And, of course, soaring levels\nof inequality."},{"time":526976,"text":"All of that, of course, is going to put\na terrific amount of stress"},{"time":531033,"text":"on the fabric of society."},{"time":532974,"text":"But beyond that, there's also\na fundamental economic problem,"},{"time":536057,"text":"and that arises because jobs\nare currently the primary mechanism"},{"time":541276,"text":"that distributes income,\nand therefore purchasing power,"},{"time":544845,"text":"to all the consumers that buy the products\nand services we're producing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550831,"text":"In order to have a vibrant market economy,"},{"time":553370,"text":"you've got to have\nlots and lots of consumers"},{"time":555514,"text":"that are really capable of buying\nthe products and services"},{"time":558567,"text":"that are being produced."},{"time":559742,"text":"If you don't have that,\nthen you run the risk"},{"time":562152,"text":"of economic stagnation,"},{"time":563591,"text":"or maybe even a declining economic spiral,"},{"time":567284,"text":"as there simply aren't enough\ncustomers out there"},{"time":569622,"text":"to buy the products\nand services being produced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572105,"text":"It's really important to realize"},{"time":574057,"text":"that all of us as individuals rely\non access to that market economy"},{"time":580095,"text":"in order to be successful."},{"time":581848,"text":"You can visualize that by thinking\nin terms of one really exceptional person."},{"time":586308,"text":"Imagine for a moment you take,\nsay, Steve Jobs,"},{"time":589320,"text":"and you drop him\non an island all by himself."},{"time":591925,"text":"On that island, he's going\nto be running around,"},{"time":594243,"text":"gathering coconuts just like anyone else."},{"time":596805,"text":"He's really not going to be\nanything special,"},{"time":599017,"text":"and the reason, of course,\nis that there is no market"},{"time":602213,"text":"for him to scale\nhis incredible talents across."},{"time":605023,"text":"So access to this market\nis really critical to us as individuals,"},{"time":608517,"text":"and also to the entire system\nin terms of it being sustainable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613063,"text":"So the question then becomes:\nWhat exactly could we do about this?"},{"time":617285,"text":"And I think you can view this\nthrough a very utopian framework."},{"time":620541,"text":"You can imagine a future\nwhere we all have to work less,"},{"time":623208,"text":"we have more time for leisure,"},{"time":626233,"text":"more time to spend with our families,"},{"time":628185,"text":"more time to do things that we find\ngenuinely rewarding"},{"time":631464,"text":"and so forth."},{"time":632645,"text":"And I think that's a terrific vision."},{"time":634524,"text":"That's something that we should\nabsolutely strive to move toward."},{"time":638177,"text":"But at the same time, I think\nwe have to be realistic,"},{"time":640877,"text":"and we have to realize"},{"time":642294,"text":"that we're very likely to face\na significant income distribution problem."},{"time":647178,"text":"A lot of people are likely\nto be left behind."},{"time":651186,"text":"And I think that in order\nto solve that problem,"},{"time":653614,"text":"we're ultimately going\nto have to find a way"},{"time":655736,"text":"to decouple incomes from traditional work."},{"time":658366,"text":"And the best, more straightforward\nway I know to do that"},{"time":661256,"text":"is some kind of a guaranteed income\nor universal basic income."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664848,"text":"Now, basic income is becoming\na very important idea."},{"time":667360,"text":"It's getting a lot\nof traction and attention,"},{"time":669523,"text":"there are a lot of important\npilot projects"},{"time":671820,"text":"and experiments going on\nthroughout the world."},{"time":674628,"text":"My own view is that a basic income\nis not a panacea;"},{"time":677852,"text":"it's not necessarily\na plug-and-play solution,"},{"time":680408,"text":"but rather, it's a place to start."},{"time":682067,"text":"It's an idea that we can\nbuild on and refine."},{"time":684873,"text":"For example, one thing that I have\nwritten quite a lot about"},{"time":687714,"text":"is the possibility of incorporating\nexplicit incentives into a basic income."},{"time":692930,"text":"To illustrate that,"},{"time":694123,"text":"imagine that you are a struggling\nhigh school student."},{"time":696915,"text":"Imagine that you are at risk\nof dropping out of school."},{"time":700289,"text":"And yet, suppose you know\nthat at some point in the future,"},{"time":703691,"text":"no matter what,"},{"time":704939,"text":"you're going to get the same\nbasic income as everyone else."},{"time":708660,"text":"Now, to my mind, that creates\na very perverse incentive"},{"time":711726,"text":"for you to simply give up\nand drop out of school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714247,"text":"So I would say, let's not\nstructure things that way."},{"time":716776,"text":"Instead, let's pay people who graduate\nfrom high school somewhat more"},{"time":722116,"text":"than those who simply drop out."},{"time":724329,"text":"And we can take that idea of building\nincentives into a basic income,"},{"time":727831,"text":"and maybe extend it to other areas."},{"time":729522,"text":"For example, we might create\nan incentive to work in the community"},{"time":733123,"text":"to help others,"},{"time":734305,"text":"or perhaps to do positive\nthings for the environment,"},{"time":737393,"text":"and so forth."},{"time":738587,"text":"So by incorporating incentives\ninto a basic income,"},{"time":741622,"text":"we might actually improve it,"},{"time":743275,"text":"and also, perhaps, take at least\na couple of steps"},{"time":745925,"text":"towards solving another problem"},{"time":748374,"text":"that I think we're quite possibly\ngoing to face in the future,"},{"time":751342,"text":"and that is, how do we all find\nmeaning and fulfillment,"},{"time":755118,"text":"and how do we occupy our time"},{"time":757460,"text":"in a world where perhaps\nthere's less demand for traditional work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":762201,"text":"So by extending and refining\na basic income,"},{"time":765030,"text":"I think we can make it look better,"},{"time":767390,"text":"and we can also, perhaps, make it\nmore politically and socially acceptable"},{"time":772712,"text":"and feasible --"},{"time":773900,"text":"and, of course, by doing that,"},{"time":775398,"text":"we increase the odds\nthat it will actually come to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779731,"text":"I think one of the most fundamental,"},{"time":782025,"text":"almost instinctive objections"},{"time":784217,"text":"that many of us have\nto the idea of a basic income,"},{"time":787694,"text":"or really to any significant\nexpansion of the safety net,"},{"time":791450,"text":"is this fear that we're going to end up\nwith too many people"},{"time":795234,"text":"riding in the economic cart,"},{"time":796996,"text":"and not enough people pulling that cart."},{"time":799067,"text":"And yet, really, the whole point\nI'm making here, of course,"},{"time":801925,"text":"is that in the future,"},{"time":803310,"text":"machines are increasingly going\nto be capable of pulling that cart for us."},{"time":807160,"text":"That should give us more options"},{"time":809174,"text":"for the way we structure\nour society and our economy,"},{"time":813009,"text":"And I think eventually, it's going to go\nbeyond simply being an option,"},{"time":816475,"text":"and it's going to become an imperative."},{"time":818400,"text":"The reason, of course,\nis that all of this is going to put"},{"time":821246,"text":"such a degree of stress on our society,"},{"time":823284,"text":"and also because jobs are that mechanism"},{"time":825822,"text":"that gets purchasing power to consumers"},{"time":827811,"text":"so they can then drive the economy."},{"time":830351,"text":"If, in fact, that mechanism\nbegins to erode in the future,"},{"time":833922,"text":"then we're going to need to replace\nit with something else"},{"time":836761,"text":"or we're going to face the risk"},{"time":838348,"text":"that our whole system simply\nmay not be sustainable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840939,"text":"But the bottom line here\nis that I really think"},{"time":843345,"text":"that solving these problems,"},{"time":845805,"text":"and especially finding a way\nto build a future economy"},{"time":849229,"text":"that works for everyone,"},{"time":851266,"text":"at every level of our society,"},{"time":853151,"text":"is going to be one of the most important\nchallenges that we all face"},{"time":856715,"text":"in the coming years and decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858782,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860054,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}